00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:04,480
Thank God you showed up when you did.

271
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:05,760
He's insane.

272
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:07,920
Do you think we should call the police?

273
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,680
No, don't worry about it.

274
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,160
I'll call my friend and have him take care of it.

275
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:14,240
I can't believe he was talking to you all these years.

276
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,280
What a nut job.

277
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,560
I know.

278
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:18,960
Well, he said I'm not pregnant.

279
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:21,840
I'm sorry if I got you all worked up over nothing.

280
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:24,720
I want you to know that I didn't do it on purpose.

281
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,680
Don't apologize.

282
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:27,840
From the moment I met you,

283
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:30,480
not a day has gone by when I haven't thought of you.

284
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:32,400
And now that I'm with you again, I'm just...

285
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,200
I'm just scared Veronica.

286
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,120
The closer I get to you, the worse it gets.

287
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,520
The thought of not being with you.

288
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:42,400
I mean, I just can't handle it.

289
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:44,160
We were made for each other Veronica.

290
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,000
You're my everything.

291
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,440
My soul mate.

292
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,360
What can I do?

293
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,800
Just hold me.

294
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:53,520
I'll always be here for you no matter what.

295
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:57,920
And together, we can tackle whatever life throws at us.

296
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,440
I believe in our Stephen.

297
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:01,760
I'm so happy to hear that.

298
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,760
I know we belong together.

299
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,440
I love you so much.

300
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,440
I love you.

301
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:27,680
Okay, Erica, so what do you think got shot?

302
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:31,600
I don't know, but I'm starting to think this story is becoming a soap opera.

303
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:35,600
Well, it certainly is and well, what do you guys think happened?

304
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,400
Or who do you think got shot or who did the shoot it?

305
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,840
Who shot who maybe?

306
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,040
What's it even a gunshot?

307
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,680
Maybe it was just a car.

308
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:44,960
The tire could have popped.

309
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:45,920
I don't know.

310
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:51,439
So we'll come to our website, tell us what you think happens or what you would like to happen

311
00:12:51,439 --> 00:12:57,120
because I know many people are expecting a little bit more romance maybe unless drama.

312
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:00,719
But if you have any questions about the language in this lesson,

313
00:13:00,719 --> 00:13:03,120
please visit the website at EnglishPod.com.

314
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:06,880
Exactly, Erica and I are always there to answer your questions and

315
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:08,479
well, anything you guys need.

316
00:13:08,479 --> 00:13:09,439
Anything?

317
00:13:09,439 --> 00:13:09,920
Anything.

318
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,760
Well, thanks for listening to this lesson and until next time.

319
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:14,319
Goodbye.

